{
  "document": {
    "aggregate_severity": {
      "text": "Moderate"
    },
    "category": "csaf_security_advisory",
    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for libarchive.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The libarchive programming library can create and read several different\nstreaming archive formats, including GNU tar, cpio, and ISO 9660 CD-ROM images.\nLibarchive is used notably in the bsdtar utility, scripting language bindings\nsuch as python-libarchive, and several popular desktop file managers.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libarchive: an out-of-bounds read via the component zipx_lzma_alone_init\n(CVE-2022-26280)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS\nscore, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s)\nlisted in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
